<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1778,2093]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,462,1778,1804]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1860" box="[462,660,1778,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elodes">
<emphasis box="[462,660,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Euphorbia elodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[819,887,1778,1804]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Distrito Federal, 
<collectingRegion box="[1092,1160,1778,1804]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Goiás</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1170,1322,1778,1804]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1333,1448,1778,1804]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[136,299,1814,1840]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[354,435,1814,1840]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Paraná</collectingRegion>
). In the State of 
<collectingRegion box="[620,733,1814,1840]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
it occurs in high montane habitats, frequently on swampy areas or riversides.
</paragraph>
